<br>
What does that mean? Why do you need detaunt if you are facing the back? Why do you need high damage? All that would happen is that you would pull aggro on your leather wearing self. Forget about using DoTs. Please clarify.<br>
<br>
1. I would like to see the enervating line improved for PvE. It does very little at low to medium levels when compared to your own level. When I use a High level say 37 level and Im fighting 37 level mobs then it works fair. If they made it so when fighting purple cons in a group the debuff would lower the mobs damage by 20% - 25% that would help a lot in making us more group friendly. <br>
<br>
2. Also a new poison like withering that slowed the attack speed of a Mob considerably would help make us group friendly.<br>
<br>
3. Disguise would bring a new excitement to the class.<br>
<br>
4. So would trap picking and trap laying. Maybe based off our poison line. You are able to lay out some traps that trigger a DoT poison a snare poison or disease. wow... that would be kewl to do to a door or some other object?<br>
<br>
5. Man-able war machines. Lets say it took a couple of people to werk a boiling cauldron above a keep door. <br>
<br>
6. increase the xp we get to kill mobs in the high 30s and 40s. <br>
<br>
7. Make a PvE colessium where we could go and have gladiator battles agains Mobs like tigers and such or PvE computer controlled classes like Paladins or Infiltrators etc. With a score board and a waiting list to do battle. What a great place to be entertained. We could barter while we were there. And place bets on fights etc. Trade wares.<br>
<br>
8. Make a RvR Collesium that you couldn't attack each other unless you entered a contest by list. Maybe have 1 on 1 battles or 3 on 3 or 8 on 8 max. Divide the Colessium into 3 section (Hib, Mid, Alb) so they could taunt each other without attacking. And sign up for a battle if they are brave. Could there be language transators? Maybe that would exploit some type of cheat. So keep the taunting in giberish then.<br>
<br>
hmmm<br>
